<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">
<html>
<head>
<title>Help: Downloading invoices</title>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<link href="../style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css">
</head>

<body>
<p class="titlebold">Downloading invoices</p>
<p class="text">To download order invoices:</p>
<ol>
  <li class="text"> Click on View under the Orders
    section in the main manager menu. </li>
  <li class="text">Select the search criteria for the orders you want to view
    and click the &quot;View Orders&quot; button. </li>
  <li class="text">Select the checkbox
      to the left of each order you want to download the invoices for. </li>
  <li class="text">Choose
      &quot;Download Invoices&quot; from the menu at the top right of the list of orders
      and press
          the Go button. </li>
  <li class="text">Choose a format to download the invoices in. Options are CSV,
    Word, or in a browser window.</li>
</ol>
<p class="text"><strong>Note: Apple's Safari browser doesn't currently work for
    downloading invoices. This is the only known feature that doesn't work with
    Safari 1.0.</strong></p>
</body>
</html>
